topLevelComment.text:
My ball won't bounce back after colliding with the brick. It just ram them down in one swap.
PS.: Nevermind. I just put this on the OnCollisionEnter2D and it worked pretty fine:

void OnCollisionEnter2D(Collision2D other)
 {
  if (other.transform.CompareTag("Brick"))
  {
   Debug.Log ("Colliding with a brick");
   rb.velocity = new Vector2 (rb.velocity.x, -rb.velocity.y);
   Destroy(other.gameObject);
  }
 }

Addendum:

If you want to stop the ball from muving during level transition (which you should, as players can lose lives if the ball hits the bottom during that time, since you can't move the paddle), then just add this line to the void Update function in the BallScript:
  if(GM.gameOver){
   transform.position = paddle.position;
  }

This is the same line used with the if (!inplay), and will put the ball on top of the paddle, however, it will launch automatically when the next level starts.
Enjoy!
